Build a WHERE query

Build part of a WHERE query using StringBuilder.
If a parameter is null, then it shouldn't be included in the query.

Example:

{name=Johnson, country=United States, city=Los Angeles, age=null}
Result:
name = 'Johnson' and country = 'United States' and city = 'Los Angeles'

Requirements:
•	The getQuery method must have one Map parameter.
•	The getQuery method must return a String.
•	The getQuery method must be static.
•	The getQuery method must return a string built according to the rules specified in the task conditions.



